The paper discusses privacy-preserving machine learning and Blockchain technology, which are relevant to several sub-categories in computer science. The focus on privacy and security suggests that cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) is the most likely category. The use of machine learning and data management also suggests cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.DB (Databases). The discussion of network architecture and interoperability suggests cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) and cs.CY (Computers and Society).
